RACE.FOOTNOTES: HEIR TO THE ROAR was off a touch slowly, advanced four wide around the turn, took the lead in upper stretch, drew clear leaving the eighth pole, drifted in nearing the sixteenth marker and widened. DEMURELY dueled inside to midstretch, could not match strides with the winner from there but fought on to hold the place. NOBLE DREAMER stalked the pace three wide, bid between foes nearing the quarter pole, vied inside of the winner past the eighth pole, steadied nearing the sixteenth pole and was outfinished for the place. DANCING DOLL broke a bit awkwardly, raced off the pace two wide, swung widest in upper stretch and lacked the needed rally. HIALEAH HOTTIE chased the pace from the rail and faded in the stretch. SPONGER dueled two wide and faltered in the lane. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY AND REVIEWED AN OBJECTION LODGED BY THE RIDER OF NOBLE DREAMER AGAINST THE WINNER FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH AND FOUND NO REASON TO ALTER THE ORIGINAL ORDER OF FINISH.
